lass=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike.re\">RCLike.re</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike.re\">RCLike.re</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Cauchy–Schwarz inequality**.\nWe need this for the `PreInnerProductSpace.Core` structure to prove the triangle inequality below\nwhen showing the core is a normed group and to take the quotient.\n\n(This is not intended for general use; see `Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Basic` for a variety of\nversions of Cauchy-Schwarz for an inner product space, rather than a `PreInnerProductSpace.Core`).\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.inner_mul_inner_self_le","kind":"theorem","line":342,"name":"InnerProductSpace.Core.inner_mul_inner_self_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.lean#L342-L368"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.cauchy_schwarz_aux\"><span class=\"name\">InnerProductSpace</span>.<span class=\"name\">Core</span>.<span class=\"name\">cauchy_schwarz_aux</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike\">RCLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#PreInnerProductSpace.Core\">PreInnerProductSpace.Core</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x </span><span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.normSq\">normSq</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.normSq\">normSq</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.normSq\">normSq</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.normSq\">normSq</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Another auxiliary equality related with the **Cauchy–Schwarz inequality**: the square of the\nseminorm of `⟪x, y⟫ • x - ⟪x, x⟫ • y` is equal to `‖x‖ ^ 2 * (‖x‖ ^ 2 * ‖y‖ ^ 2 - ‖⟪x, y⟫‖ ^ 2)`.\nWe use `InnerProductSpace.ofCore.normSq x` etc. (defeq to `is_R_or_C.re ⟪x, x⟫`) instead of\n`‖x‖ ^ 2` etc. to avoid extra rewrites when applying it to an `InnerProductSpace`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.cauchy_schwarz_aux","kind":"theorem","line":329,"name":"InnerProductSpace.Core.cauchy_schwarz_aux","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.lean#L329-L340"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#InnerProductSpace.Core.cauchy_schwarz_aux'\"><span class=\"name\">InnerProductSpace</span>.<span class=\"name\">Core</span>.<span class=\"name\">cauchy_schwarz_aux'</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#RCLike\">RCLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\